Andromeda has a D25 isophotal diameter of about 46.56 kiloparsecs (152,000 light-years) and is approximately 765 kpc (2.5 million light-years) from Earth.
Also termed as NGC 224, it is expected to collide with the Milky Way Galaxy in 4-5 billion years.
With an apparent magnitude of 3.4, this galaxy is visible with naked eyes under right conditions. 
This G-Drive contains the Fits file for it - https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1kAZJRS1SjPyxJOKTyHckUpXy0GdvhZBB?usp=sharing
